---

Trim the @spring onion{1} then slice thinly. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Trim the @green beans{80} then chop into thirds.

Drain and rinse the @chickpeas{1%400g can} in a #sieve{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat.

Add half the spring onion and all the green beans and stir-fry until starting to
soften, ~{2%mins}.

Stir in the garlic and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @?sugar{pinch}. Cook for another
~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @harissa spice mix{½} and @ground turmeric{2}.

Cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add the chickpeas and @king prawns{150%g}. Stir-fry for another ~{2-3%mins}.

Finally, stir in the @steamed basmati rice{1}, breaking it up with a #spoon{}.

Stir-fry until the rice is piping hot and the prawns are cooked through,
~{3-4%mins}.

> The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} if needed.

Serve the Moroccan prawn rice in #bowls{} topped with a dollop of
@low fat natural yoghurt{75%g} and the remaining spring onion. Enjoy!